<div><div><h4>Job Description</h4></div><div><div><span><div><div>Responsibilities:</div><div><div>&#8226; Responsible to create new short-term tenancy/manage existing tenancies within undeveloped land banks to ensure generation of sustainable income for the company.</div><div><br />&#8226; Responsible to conduct site inspection/surveillance monitoring within undeveloped land banks to avoid encroachment by squatters, illegal activities which can cause inability to hand over vacant possession to Project Team/JV Co/new owner and unexpected cost for eviction proceeding/compensation.&#160;</div><div><br />&#8226; Renting vacant undeveloped land banks/pocket land for short-term agricultural activities/business to generate sustainable revenue:<br />- Scout and identify prospective tenants looking to rent land for short-term<br />- Provide potential tenants with information on land and a site inspection to view/observe features/suitability of the site in order to convince customers and influence lease<br />- Run background checks on potential tenants (if company) to identify the ownership, registered address, business, evaluate their financial capability.<br />- Provide application form and brief the process flow, standard terms &amp; conditions of the agreement, rental rates, payment, security deposit, etc.<br />- Consult Project team/Business Development/B2B on potential development plan/land sale and availability of the land for the proposed tenancy&#160;&#160;&#160;<br />- Prepare proposal/management paper seeking approval to rent the land to the potential tenant&#160;<br />- Prepare draft Letter of Offer (LOO)/Tenancy Agreement (TA) based on standard template/guide from existing tenancies<br />- Consult/seek assistance from superior to review/amend and finalise the document for execution.<br />- Attend signing for acceptance of the LOO/TA by the Tenant and ensure payment of the security deposit &amp; 1st month rental&#160;&#160;&#160;<br />- Monitor collection report of the monthly rental with Finance Department, issue reminder to tenant for nonpayment/outstanding rental&#160;&#160;<br />- Monitor activity at site on periodic basis to ensure compliance of terms &amp; condition, issue reminder/notice for breach or non-conformance&#160;&#160;&#160;<br />- Communicate and negotiate with tenant for extension of term, revision of rental or termination, 3 months (at least 1 month) before the expiry of tenancy<br />- Ensure timely handing over vacant possession of the land to Project team if the land is required for development or hand over to new owner/JV Co if the land is affected by land sale</div><div>&#8226; To plan surveillance program/conduct frequent site monitoring to avoid undeveloped land banks/pocket land encroached by squatters/illegal activities:&#160;<br />- Identified land boundary, potential location exposed to encroachment (primary &amp; secondary area) for planning of surveillance program/setting frequency of inspection<br />- Security Measures and Enhancing Public Awareness - identified potential encroachment area for installation of boom gate, blockage, earth drain, fencing and signboard.<br />- Issue Notice to Vacate to the illegal occupants<br />- Coordinate with UEMS AP to execute enforcement to demolish/torn down structures at site<br />- Seek advice from superior/Legal Department, prepare proposal/management paper to seek approval from management to appoint Solicitor for filing of eviction proceeding at High Court (in the event of retaliation/challenge/counter claim by the trespasser)&#160;&#160;</div><div>&#8226; Execute/perform administrative function for Interim Business team:<br />- Record all incoming and outgoing document<br />- Maintain document in the filing system so as to ensure documents safe keeping and easy retrieval<br />- Manage the safekeeping of surveillance equipment, maintenance of vehicle<br />- Other administrative works in the Unit/Department</div></div><div>Requirements:</div><div>&#8226; Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree in Valuation/ Land Management/Property Management or any other related discipline.</div><div>&#8226; At least 1 year(s) of working experience with minimum 1 year in development company/developer/Enforcement Authority (Police, Army, etc.) is required for this position.</div><div>&#8226; Possess good communication skills and able to work independently.</div><div>&#8226; Having good relationship/PR with local Enforcement Authority is an added advantage.</div><div>&#8226; Full-Time and Contract position(s) available.</div></div></span></div></div></div>
